{
  "id": "york-ycjd-compressor",
  "brand": "York",
  "model": "YCJD36S41S1",
  "equipment_type": "ac-condenser",
  "symptom": "Outdoor unit contactor pulls in but compressor does not start. Condenser fan runs. Loud humming or buzzing from the compressor for 5\u201310 seconds, then the circuit breaker trips or the overload clicks off. Unit is hot to the touch near the compressor.",
  "diagnosis": "Compressor with open or shorted winding, or mechanically locked rotor. Check winding resistance: C-R + C-S should equal R-S (within 2 ohms). Mega-ohm test to ground \u2014 <1 M\u03a9 = grounded winding. If windings test OK, compressor is mechanically seized (internal bearing failure).",
  "part_number": "S1-01504270000 (York/JCI scroll compressor, 3-ton) \u2014 requires recovery, brazing, vacuum, and recharge",
  "procedure": [
    "Kill power at the disconnect. Wait 5 minutes for the internal overload to reset.",
    "Remove the compressor terminal cover. Inspect for burn marks or melted plastic \u2014 indicates electrical failure.",
    "Using a multimeter on R\u00d71 scale, measure winding resistance between all three terminals: C-R, C-S, R-S.",
    "C-R + C-S should approximately equal R-S. If any winding reads open (OL) or very low (<0.5 ohm), the compressor is electrically failed.",
    "Mega-ohm test: measure from each terminal to the compressor shell/ground. Reading <1 M\u03a9 = grounded winding \u2014 compressor must be replaced.",
    "If windings test OK: try a hard-start kit (potential relay + start capacitor). If it starts, the motor is weak but functional \u2014 recommend replacement anyway.",
    "If compressor is confirmed failed: recover all refrigerant, cut and braze the suction and discharge lines, remove the old compressor (heavy \u2014 use a dolly).",
    "Install replacement compressor, braze connections, pressure test with nitrogen, evacuate to 500 microns, recharge by weight.",
    "Add correct oil charge (POE oil, check spec \u2014 typically 32 oz for this unit).",
    "Start the unit, check amp draw against nameplate RLA/LRA. Monitor for 30 minutes."
  ],
  "safety_notes": [
    "Compressor terminals carry line voltage \u2014 verify power is dead before removing the terminal cover.",
    "A grounded compressor can energize the chassis \u2014 always test before touching.",
    "Compressor replacement involves brazing under nitrogen \u2014 fire extinguisher must be on site.",
    "This is a major repair \u2014 recommend quoting the customer before proceeding. Flag scope change if original work order was for a different issue."
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 180,
  "tags": [
    "compressor",
    "won't start",
    "locked rotor",
    "trips breaker",
    "humming",
    "york",
    "YCJD",
    "winding test",
    "mega-ohm"
  ],
